Out[3]:
Index(['Subject ID', 'MRI ID', 'Group', 'Visit', 'MR Delay', 'M/F', 'Hand',
       'Age', 'EDUC', 'SES', 'MMSE', 'CDR', 'eTIV', 'nWBV', 'ASF'],
      dtype='object')
Column Description: Subject Id:patient identification number Mri ID: number of the Mri scans taken Group: Demented,non-demented,converted(initially non-demented and later demented) CDR: Clinical Dementia Rating, with 0, 0.5,1,2 corresponding to nondemented, very mild,mild AD,moderate AD MMSE: Mini-Mental State Examination where scores range from 30 (best) to 0 (worst) Educ: years of education Visit: total no.of visits Etiv: estimated total intracranial volume NWBV: Normalised whole brain volume ASF: Atlas scaling factor Age: 18-96 yrs mr Delay: time interval between successive scans with in an year.Mr delay will be zero for initial visit.

In [17]:
def categorize_Mmse(Mmse):
  if  19<= Mmse <=23 :
    return "mild cognitive impairement"
  elif 10 <= Mmse <= 18:
    return "moderate cognitive impairement "
  elif 0< Mmse <= 9:
    return "severe cognitive impairement"
  elif 24 <= Mmse <= 30:
    return "Normal cognition"
  

data['Dementia_category_Mmse'] = data['Mmse'].apply(lambda x: categorize_Mmse(x))
In [18]:
def categorize_Cdr(Cdr):
  if  Cdr <=0 :
    return "Non-demented"
  elif 0.1 < Cdr <= 0.5:
    return "mild demented"
  elif 0.6 < Cdr <= 1:
    return "very mild demented"
  elif 1.1 < Cdr <= 2:
    return "moderate dementia"
  elif 2.1 < Cdr <= 3:
    return "Severe dementia"

data['Dementia_category_Cdr'] = data['Cdr'].apply(lambda x: categorize_Cdr(x))
